We’re trying to debug our robot, but none of our print statements seem to make it to the Rio Log. We have also tried to use Commands.print as well, and we don’t see anything.

We can tell from the robots behavior that code is flowing through the area, it just seems like our messages aren’t making it into the log. This obviously makes it a real PITA to debug.

Are there any known issues with e.g. IO buffering from the JVM to the Rio Log? Any secret methods for getting log output to show up?

Hi gang! Sorry to take so long getting back to this thread - competitions intervened and we had a lot of stuff going on.

I don’t have specific code to show off - we’ve moved all of our debugging to SmartDashboard since we couldn’t get the log output to show. Roughly speaking, we’ve tried the following:

  • Using System.err.println. I always use err because it’s unbuffered, and that’s rubbed off on the team.

  • Using Commands.print. We’re definitely aware of the difference between Commands and method calls. We included these commands as part of a SequentialGroupCommand to see if we could figure out where we were getting hung up.

At this point, I’m prepared to believe that the log statements didn’t show up because the code was never reached.

In a nutshell, our arm would “calibrate” itself, which ended when it bumped up against a couple of limit switches the find a “home” position. For whatever reason, those limit switches were really temperamental, and wound up getting bent out of shape, or having the DIO plug come loose. The result was Commands that would never finish.

The main thing I was looking for is confirmation on how things are supposed to work. Should I expect stdout and stderr from my code to show up in the Rio log? In the Driver Station log? Both? Neither?

epeters1111:

Should I expect stdout and stderr from my code to show up in the Rio log? In the Driver Station log? Both? Neither?

Both. They come from the same source. Note in the DS you need to open the full console window (via the gear icon) to see print statements.
